cs.CY, cs.CR, cs.SE, cs.DB, cs.LG 

This paper discusses the legal, commercial, and technical aspects of data portability in the context of the Internet of Things (IoT). It focuses on the need for information privacy by design and default (PbD) for personal data-driven technologies, which falls under the category of cybersecurity (cs.CR) and software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also discusses data management architectures, tools, and platforms, which are related to databases (cs.DB) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper addresses regulatory challenges, which could fall under the category of computer and society (cs.CY).
